quran[78]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Merciful
  55,2,taught the Qur'an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,taught him plain speech
  55,5,The sun and the moon have their appointed time
  55,6,The herbs and the trees adore
  55,7,"And the heavens, He raised them and set the balance"
  55,8,that ye should not be outrageous in the balance
  55,9,"But weigh ye aright, and stint not the balance"
  55,10,And the earth He has set it for living creatures
  55,11,"therein are fruits and palms, with sheaths"
  55,12,and grain with chaff and frequent shoots
  55,13,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,14,He created men of crackling clay like the potters
  55,15,And He created the ginn from smokeless fire
  55,16,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,17,The Lord of the two easts and the Lord of the two wests
  55,18,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,19,He has let loose the two seas that meet together
  55,20,between them is a barrier they cannot pass
  55,21,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,22,He brings forth from each pearls both large and small
  55,23,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,24,His are the ships which rear aloft in the sea like mountains
  55,25,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,26,Every one upon it is transient
  55,27,but the face of thy Lord endowed with majesty and honour shall endure
  55,28,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,29,Of Him whosoever is in the heaven and the earth does beg; every day He is in (some fresh) business
  55,30,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,31,"We shall be at leisure for you, O ye two weighty ones"
  55,32,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,33,O assembly of ginns and mankind! if ye are able to pass through the confines of heaven and earth then pass through them!- ye cannot pass through save by authority
  55,34,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,35,"There shall be sent against you a flash or fire, and molten copper, and ye shall not be helped"
  55,36,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,37,And when the heaven is rent asunder and become rosy red - (melting) like grease
  55,38,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,39,On that day neither man nor ginn shall be asked about his crime
  55,40,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,41,"The sinners shall be known by their marks, and shall be seized by the forelock and the feet"
  55,42,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,43,"This is hell, which the sinners did call a lie"
  55,44,they shall circulate between it and water boiling quite
  55,45,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,46,But for him who fears the station of his Lord are gardens twain
  55,47,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,48,Both furnished with branching trees
  55,49,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,50,In each are flowing springs
  55,51,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,52,"In each are, of every fruit, two kinds"
  55,53,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,54,"Reclining on beds the linings of which are of brocade, and the fruit of the two gardens within reach to cull"
  55,55,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,56,Therein are maids of modest glances whom no man nor ginn has deflowered before
  55,57,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,58,As though they were rubies and pearls
  55,59,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,60,Is the reward of goodness aught but goodness
  55,61,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,62,"And besides these, are gardens twain"
  55,63,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,64,With dark green foliage
  55,65,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,66,In each two gushing springs
  55,67,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,68,In each fruit and palms and pomegranates
  55,69,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,70,In them maidens best and fairest
  55,71,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,72,Bright and large-eyed maids kept in their tents
  55,73,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,74,Whom no man nor ginn has deflowered before them
  55,75,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,76,Reclining on green cushions and beautiful carpets
  55,77,Then which of your Lord's bounties will ye twain deny
  55,78,Blessed be the name of thy Lord possessed of majesty and honour